"{\"correct\": \"no\", \"explanation\": \"The 'metric' parameter in DBSCAN is expected to be a callable that takes two arrays as input and returns a distance value. However, the 'get_point_distance' function returns an array from 'euclidean_distances', which does not match the expected return type. It should return a single distance value instead of an array.\", \"patch\": \"26c26\\n<     return euclidean_distances([p1.to_list()], [p2.to_list()])\\n---\\n>     return euclidean_distances([p1.to_list()], [p2.to_list()])[0][0]\"}"